(1/2) Okay so I was going to wait to post till I officially hit my goal  but I’ve been getting a lot of comments on my appearance so I figured it was time to share. If you’re new here you may not know October 1st 2017 was quite frankly the worst day of my life. Me and my family were in the largest mass shooting in American history. Something I never thought I’d have to survive or live through. Along with that came many mental healthy struggles. I had sever anxiety which I was placed on medication for. During the last few years of faced a lot of dark depression. Due to my mental state and a lot of changes to my body. Stress causes weight gain. For me 80lbs of weight gain. January of this year I decided to work my butt off to get this trauma off my body. To be frank with you diet and exercise didn’t work. I fully was ready to give up. My amazing supporter and boyfriend said something might be wrong and maybe I should see a doctor. As healthy as I eat and as much as I workout I should be dropping pounds. I finally mustarded up the courage to see a doctor and in fact something was 100% wrong. My cortisol hormone was unbalanced which can be cause by a traumatic life event or a lot of stress. My hormone basically cause my blood sugar and insulin to be elevated and be a pre diabetic. The doctor stressed if I came in a couple months later it would have be too late and I would have been diagnosed as a diabetic. For me that was the scariest thing to hear. I knew something was wrong with my body and hormones but I was too afraid to go to a doctor rather than getting answers to fix it. I was place on medication (Ozempic) to level out my blood sugar and insulin following a healthy diet (80/20) let’s be real I’m not perfect with eating lol & a lot of working out. I’ve also cut back on drinking. Maybe 1-2 drinks a month. So here I am 60lbs down 20 more to go to my goal weight.
